  <h1>
   clamp
  </h1>
  With this function you can maintain an input value between a specified range.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">clamp(val, min, max)
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      val
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The value to clamp.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      min
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The minimum value to clamp between.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      max
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The maximum value to clamp between.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">speed = clamp(speed, 1, 10);
</code></pre>
  The above code will clamp the speed so that it never falls below 1 or goes over 10.
 </body>
